{
  "text": "By the previous proposition, Theorem 1.1 is reduced to the problem of finding suitable mild gaps of f ℓ,ℓ . In this section we present a proposition that provides \"many\" mild gaps of a prescribed type. This result is proved via an elementary technique known as the Maier matrix method [CITATION_1] . We require the following definition: for every m ∈ Z and M ∈ N + let",
